## 9. Migration Strategy

### Phase 1: Preparation
- [ ] Audit current PF5 usage
- [ ] Identify breaking changes that affect the project
- [ ] Plan migration approach
- [ ] Set up testing environment

### Phase 2: Package Updates
- [ ] Update package.json dependencies
- [ ] Run available codemods
- [ ] Fix compilation errors

### Phase 3: Manual Updates
- [ ] Address changes not covered by codemods
- [ ] Update custom CSS/styling
- [ ] Fix TypeScript errors
- [ ] Update tests

### Phase 4: Testing & Validation
- [ ] Visual regression testing
- [ ] Functionality testing
- [ ] Performance testing
- [ ] Accessibility testing

## 10. Severity Levels

- **Critical**: Breaks compilation, requires immediate attention
- **High**: Major functionality changes, may break features
- **Medium**: Deprecated features, should be addressed
- **Low**: Cosmetic or minor changes

## 11. Project-Specific Notes

Based on the lightspeed-console-plugin project structure:

### Components to Focus On
- Chat interface components
- Modal dialogs
- Form elements
- Navigation components
- Empty states
- Buttons and interactive elements

### Areas of Concern
- Plugin-specific styling (ols-plugin__ prefixed classes)
- PatternFly integration in OpenShift Console context
- i18n compatibility
- Cypress test compatibility

### Testing Requirements
- Ensure all Cypress tests continue to work
- Verify plugin loading in OpenShift Console
- Test across different screen sizes
- Validate accessibility compliance


