<div class="verdict-banner">
  <div style="font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-muted); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; margin-bottom:8px;">PatternFly 5 → 6 Migration Comparison</div>
  <h1>🏆 Winner: <span style="color:var(--green)">semver/goose/053126-0138</span></h1>
  <p style="color:var(--text-muted); margin:0;">Decisive victory — the only branch that performed any actual migration work.</p>

  <div class="grid-2" style="max-width:600px; margin:24px auto 0;">
    <div class="card card-green score-card">
      <div class="score" style="color:var(--green);">91</div>
      <div class="label">semver/goose/053126-0138</div>
      <div class="badge badge-green" style="margin-top:8px;">WINNER</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-red score-card">
      <div class="score" style="color:var(--red);">2</div>
      <div class="label">pf-codemods-053126-0158</div>
      <div class="badge badge-red" style="margin-top:8px;">NO MIGRATION</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="verdict-reason">
    <strong style="color:var(--text)">Key reasons:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>pf-codemods</strong> made <span style="color:var(--red);font-weight:700">zero source code changes</span> — only a codemod cache artifact was committed</li>
      <li><strong>semver/goose</strong> upgraded React 17→18 (required for @patternfly/chatbot 6.x), migrated all 5 pf-v5 CSS tokens, removed all 12 @ts-expect-error suppressions, added ModalBody wrappers, fixed Dropdown/Label/MenuToggle APIs, and cleaned up deprecated patterns</li>
      <li>Both branches build successfully; unit tests pass on both</li>
      <li><strong>semver/goose</strong> introduces 5 new lint errors, but these are pre-existing code patterns newly surfaced by stricter React 18 types, not migration regressions</li>
      <li>One remaining gap in <strong>semver/goose</strong>: ConfirmationModal still uses <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code> Modal (also present in main)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

