    <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill bar-green" style="width:3%">0</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="bar-row">
    <div class="bar-label">semver/goose/053126-0138</div>
    <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill bar-orange" style="width:18%">5</div></div>
  </div>
</div>
<p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.85rem;">The 5 lint errors in the goose branch are pre-existing code patterns (setState-in-effect, throttle/debounce in useCallback) that were silently accepted by React 17 types but are flagged by the stricter <code>eslint-plugin-react-hooks@7.1.1</code> resolved with <code>@types/react@18</code>. The same code exists in main — it just isn't flagged because main uses <code>@types/react@17</code>.</p>

