</table>

<p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.85rem;">* pf-codemods gets full "Functional Preservation" marks trivially — it made no changes, so no behavior was altered. This is not a positive signal for a migration branch; it simply means the branch is equivalent to main.</p>
<p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.85rem;">† pf-codemods receives 2 total points: for the fact that it technically builds and runs tests (identical to main). Zero points are awarded for any migration category since no migration work was done.</p>
