<!-- 6. DETAILED ANALYSIS -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<section id="detailed-analysis">
<h2>6. Detailed Analysis</h2>

<!-- 6.1 Package Upgrades -->
<details id="detail-packages">
<summary>📦 Package Upgrades</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
<p><code>@patternfly/chatbot@6.x</code> requires React 18+ (<code>"react": "^18 || ^19"</code> in peerDependencies). The main branch uses React 17.0.2 with npm overrides, which is incompatible with chatbot. Core PF6 packages (<code>@patternfly/react-core</code>, etc.) support React 17+.</p>

<h4>Main branch (baseline)</h4>
<div class="code-block">"react": "17.0.2",          // pinned
"react-dom": "17.0.2",      // pinned
"@types/react": "^17.0.91", // React 17 types
"react-redux": "7.2.9",     // pinned
"react-i18next": "11.18.6", // pinned
"overrides": {
  "react": "17.0.2",        // force all deps to React 17
  "react-dom": "17.0.2"
}</div>

<h4>Per-branch comparison</h4>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Package</th><th>main</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>react</td><td>17.0.2 (pinned)</td><td style="color:var(--red)">17.0.2 (unchanged)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">^18.3.1 ✓</td></tr>
    <tr><td>react-dom</td><td>17.0.2 (pinned)</td><td style="color:var(--red)">17.0.2 (unchanged)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">^18.3.1 ✓</td></tr>
    <tr><td>@types/react</td><td>^17.0.91</td><td style="color:var(--red)">^17.0.91 (unchanged)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">^18.3.0 ✓</td></tr>
    <tr><td>react-redux</td><td>7.2.9 (pinned)</td><td style="color:var(--red)">7.2.9 (unchanged)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">^9.3.0 ✓</td></tr>
    <tr><td>react-i18next</td><td>11.18.6 (pinned)</td><td style="color:var(--red)">11.18.6 (unchanged)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">^11.12.0 (flexible)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>overrides.react</td><td>17.0.2</td><td style="color:var(--red)">17.0.2 (unchanged)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">removed ✓</td></tr>
    <tr><td>overrides.react-dom</td><td>17.0.2</td><td style="color:var(--red)">17.0.2 (unchanged)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">removed ✓</td></tr>
    <tr><td>@patternfly/react-core</td><td>6.4.1</td><td>6.4.1 (unchanged)</td><td>6.4.1 (unchanged)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>@patternfly/chatbot</td><td>6.6.0-prerelease.6</td><td>6.6.0-prerelease.6</td><td>6.6.0-prerelease.6</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p><span class="winner-tag green">Winner: semver/goose</span> — properly resolves the React 17 / chatbot 6.x incompatibility and modernizes the dependency tree.</p>
</div>
</details>

<!-- 6.2 React Version -->
<details id="detail-react">
<summary>⚛️ React Version Upgrade (17 → 18)</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>Why this matters</h4>
<p>The <code>@patternfly/chatbot@6.6.0</code> package declares <code>"react": "^18 || ^19"</code> as a peer dependency. Running it with React 17 violates the peer dependency contract and may cause runtime issues. The main branch suppresses this with <code>@ts-expect-error: TS2786</code> comments on every chatbot component usage (12 instances across GeneralPage.tsx and Prompt.tsx).</p>

<h4>semver/goose changes</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Upgraded <code>react</code> and <code>react-dom</code> from <code>17.0.2</code> → <code>^18.3.1</code></li>
  <li>Upgraded <code>@types/react</code> from <code>^17.0.91</code> → <code>^18.3.0</code></li>
  <li>Upgraded <code>react-redux</code> from <code>7.2.9</code> → <code>^9.3.0</code> (react-redux 9 supports React 18)</li>
  <li>Removed <code>overrides.react</code> and <code>overrides.react-dom</code> that forced React 17</li>
  <li>Removed all 12 <code>@ts-expect-error: TS2786</code> suppressions (now unnecessary since chatbot types are compatible)</li>
</ul>

<h4>pf-codemods changes</h4>
<p>None. React remains at 17.0.2 with overrides.</p>

<h4>Side effect analysis</h4>
<p>The React 18 upgrade causes <code>eslint-plugin-react-hooks@7.1.1</code> (resolved via semver) to enforce stricter rules than the <code>7.0.1</code> resolved with React 17 types. This surfaces 5 pre-existing issues:</p>
<ul>
  <li>3× <code>react-hooks/set-state-in-effect</code> — <code>changePod()</code> and <code>setKind()</code> called synchronously in effects</li>
  <li>2× <code>react-hooks/use-memo</code> — <code>throttle()</code> and <code>debounce()</code> not inline in <code>useCallback</code></li>
</ul>
<p>These are pre-existing code patterns; the migration correctly exposed them rather than causing them.</p>

<p><span class="winner-tag green">Winner: semver/goose</span></p>
</div>
</details>

<!-- 6.3 CSS Token Migration -->
<details id="detail-css">
<summary>🎨 CSS Token Migration (pf-v5 → pf-t)</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
<p>PatternFly 6 renamed CSS design token variables from <code>--pf-v5-global--*</code> to <code>--pf-t--global--*</code>. Old <code>pf-v5</code> variables still exist as aliases for backward compatibility, but the official upgrade guide recommends migrating to the new format. The <code>css-vars-updater</code> codemod handles this automatically.</p>

<h4>Before (main) — <code>src/components/general-page.css</code></h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-del">  padding-left: var(--pf-v5-global--spacer--md);
  padding-top: var(--pf-v5-global--spacer--form-element);
  font-family: var(--pf-v5-global--FontFamily--monospace);
  font-weight: var(--pf-v5-global--FontWeight--bold);
  margin-left: var(--pf-v5-global--spacer--sm);</span></div>

<h4>After (semver/goose)</h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-add">  padding-left: var(--pf-t--global--spacer--md);
  padding-top: var(--pf-t--global--spacer--xs);
  font-family: var(--pf-t--global--FontFamily--monospace);
  font-weight: var(--pf-t--global--font--weight--heading--bold);
  margin-left: var(--pf-t--global--spacer--200);</span></div>

<h4>Token mapping analysis</h4>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>PF5 Token</th><th>PF6 Token (goose)</th><th>Correct?</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>--pf-v5-global--spacer--md</code></td><td><code>--pf-t--global--spacer--md</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Correct</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--pf-v5-global--spacer--form-element</code></td><td><code>--pf-t--global--spacer--xs</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-orange">≈ Close</span> (no exact 1:1; xs is a reasonable substitute)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--pf-v5-global--FontFamily--monospace</code></td><td><code>--pf-t--global--FontFamily--monospace</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Correct</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--pf-v5-global--FontWeight--bold</code></td><td><code>--pf-t--global--font--weight--heading--bold</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-green">✓ Correct</span></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--pf-v5-global--spacer--sm</code></td><td><code>--pf-t--global--spacer--200</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-orange">≈ Close</span> (PF6 uses numeric scale; 200 ≈ sm)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h4>Per-branch comparison</h4>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>pf-v5 tokens migrated</td><td style="color:var(--red)">0/5</td><td style="color:var(--green)">5/5</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Remaining pf-v5 refs</td><td style="color:var(--red)">5</td><td style="color:var(--green)">0</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p><span class="winner-tag green">Winner: semver/goose</span></p>
</div>
</details>

<!-- 6.4 Modal / ModalBody -->
<details id="detail-modal">
<summary>📐 Modal / ModalBody Changes</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
<p>PF6 promotes the composable Modal from <code>ModalNext</code>. The new <code>Modal</code> requires content to be wrapped in <code>ModalBody</code>, <code>ModalHeader</code>, and <code>ModalFooter</code> subcomponents. The old single-component Modal (with <code>title</code>, <code>actions</code> props) is deprecated to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code>.</p>
<p>This app uses a custom <code>Modal</code> wrapper (via <code>react-modal</code>) for most modals. These custom modals aren't directly affected by the PF6 Modal change, but <code>ModalBody</code> should still be used inside them for proper PF6 spacing and semantics.</p>

<h4>semver/goose changes</h4>
<p>Added <code>ModalBody</code> import and wrapper to 4 modal components:</p>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>AttachEventsModal.tsx</td><td>Imported <code>ModalBody</code>, wrapped modal content</td></tr>
    <tr><td>AttachmentModal.tsx</td><td>Imported <code>ModalBody</code>, wrapped modal content</td></tr>
    <tr><td>NewChatModal.tsx</td><td>Imported <code>ModalBody</code>, wrapped modal content</td></tr>
    <tr><td>ResponseToolModal.tsx</td><td>Imported <code>ModalBody</code>, wrapped modal content</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h4>Remaining gap</h4>
<p><code>ConfirmationModal.tsx</code> still imports <code>Modal</code> from <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code> in both branches (and main). This is the one remaining deprecated import.</p>

<p><span class="winner-tag green">Winner: semver/goose</span> (4 modals migrated vs. 0)</p>
</div>
</details>

<!-- 6.5 Label icon prop -->
<details id="detail-label">
<summary>🏷️ Label icon Prop</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
<p>In PF6, the <code>Label</code> component's <code>icon</code> prop is used to render an icon before the label text. Previously, icons could be placed as children alongside text. The PF6 pattern is to use the dedicated <code>icon</code> prop.</p>

<h4>Before (main) — <code>AttachmentLabel.tsx</code></h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-del">&lt;Label className="ols-plugin__context-label" onClick={onClick} onClose={onClose}&gt;
  &lt;ResourceIcon kind={kind} /&gt;
  &lt;span className="ols-plugin__context-label-text"&gt;{name}&lt;/span&gt;</span></div>

<h4>After (semver/goose)</h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-add">&lt;Label className="ols-plugin__context-label" onClick={onClick} onClose={onClose}
  icon={&lt;ResourceIcon kind={kind} /&gt;}&gt;
  &lt;span className="ols-plugin__context-label-text"&gt;{name}&lt;/span&gt;</span></div>

<p><span class="winner-tag green">Winner: semver/goose</span> — correctly moves icon from children to <code>icon</code> prop.</p>
</div>
</details>

<!-- 6.6 MenuToggle icon prop -->
<details id="detail-menutoggle">
<summary>🔽 MenuToggle icon Prop</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
<p>In PF6, <code>MenuToggle</code> requires icons to be passed via the <code>icon</code> prop rather than as children. The codemod <code>menuToggle-warn-iconOnly-toggle</code> flags this but cannot auto-fix it.</p>

<h4>Before (main) — <code>AttachLogModal.tsx</code> PodDropdown</h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-del">&lt;MenuToggle isExpanded={isOpen} onClick={toggleIsOpen} ref={toggleRef}&gt;
  &lt;ResourceIcon kind="Pod" /&gt; {selectedPod?.metadata?.name}
&lt;/MenuToggle&gt;</span></div>

<h4>After (semver/goose)</h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-add">&lt;MenuToggle icon={&lt;ResourceIcon kind="Pod" /&gt;} isExpanded={isOpen}
  onClick={toggleIsOpen} ref={toggleRef}&gt;
  {selectedPod?.metadata?.name}
&lt;/MenuToggle&gt;</span></div>

<p>Note: The ContainerDropdown already used the <code>icon</code> prop correctly in main. Only the PodDropdown needed fixing.</p>

<p><span class="winner-tag green">Winner: semver/goose</span></p>
</div>
</details>

<!-- 6.7 Dropdown onSelect -->
<details id="detail-dropdown">
<summary>📋 Dropdown onSelect Signature</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
<p>The composable Dropdown's <code>onSelect</code> callback in PF6 has the signature <code>(event?, value?: DropdownItemProps['value']) => void</code> where <code>value</code> is <code>string | number | undefined</code>. Previously, the second parameter was typed as <code>string</code>.</p>

<h4>Before (main) — <code>AttachLogModal.tsx</code></h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-del">const onSelect = React.useCallback(
  (_e: React.MouseEvent&lt;Element, MouseEvent&gt; | undefined, newValue: string) =&gt; {
    closeDropdown();
    setContainer(newValue);
  }, ...);</span></div>

<h4>After (semver/goose)</h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-add">const onSelect = React.useCallback(
  (_e: React.MouseEvent&lt;Element, MouseEvent&gt; | undefined,
   newValue: DropdownItemProps['value']) =&gt; {
    closeDropdown();
    setContainer(newValue as string);
  }, ...);</span></div>

<p>Applied to both ContainerDropdown and PodDropdown <code>onSelect</code> handlers. The <code>DropdownItemProps</code> import was also added.</p>

<p><span class="winner-tag green">Winner: semver/goose</span></p>
</div>
</details>

<!-- 6.8 ClipboardCopyButton -->
<details id="detail-clipboard">
<summary>📋 ClipboardCopyButton textId Removal</summary>
<div class="details-content">
<h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
<p>The <code>textId</code> prop on <code>ClipboardCopyButton</code> is deprecated in PF6. It should be removed.</p>

<h4>Before (main) — <code>CopyAction.tsx</code></h4>
<div class="code-block"><span class="code-del">&lt;ClipboardCopyButton
  ...
  onTooltipHidden={setNotCopied}
  textId="code-content"
  variant="plain"
&gt;</span></div>

